<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 04 at 8:04PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of east central
Roosevelt and eastern Sheridan Counties through 900 PM MDT...
At 804 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles east of Port Of Raymond to 6 miles
northeast of Froid. Movement was east at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Medicine Lake, Froid, Westby, Reserve, Dagmar, Dooley, Antelope,
Comertown and Coalridge.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
